    "long_instructions": "### The “Surprise Cue” Challenge: Turning Mistakes into Creative Opportunities\r\n\r\nGreat performers know that surprises—planned or not—are part of the magic of live music. Just like a DJ adjusting a mix on the fly or a band improvising during a concert, you'll practice reacting to unexpected changes in your performance by using the new `random` block.\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/589b9aa091a4c02498a0a87f45d3d5aa-image-1742321504908.11.38 AM.png)\r\n\r\n**Do This**:\r\n- Choose three sounds and pair each with a sound action. (For example: when the cowbell plays, add a delay filter and trigger a blip sound.)\r\n- Add your three sounds into the `play random` block. \r\n- Set up your triggers so there's an action for each sound in your `play random` block.\r\n- Perform! As you play, react in real-time to each sound cue, adjusting your timing and effects as needed.\r\n\r\n",
